==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tappet
<hw>Tap"pet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A
lever or projection moved by some other piece, as a cam, or intended to
tap or touch something else, with a view to produce change or regulate
motion.</def> <rj><au>G. Francis.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tappet motion</b></col>, <cd>a valve motion worked by
tappets from a reciprocating part, without an eccentric or cam, -- used
in steam pumps, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tappet rod</ent>⟦br⟧
